Ranger Help for: camp
=====================

SUMMARY:
Set up a persistent camp at your current location. Your camp becomes
your login point - when you log back in, you'll appear at your camp
instead of the guild lodge. Other Rangers can see where your camp is
and can visit using 'trailblaze to camp <name>'. Your tent will show
your name so others know whose camp it is.

USAGE:
  camp                  Set up camp (requires unpacked tent)
  camp break            Break camp and return login to the lodge
  camp stores           Review wildcraft supplies and camp stores
  camp stock            Turn field supplies into camp supplies
  camp cook <food>      Cook a temporary meal for the road
  camp brew <drink>     Brew a temporary drink for the road
  camp tend             Recover hit points and spell points at camp
  camp ward             Raise a temporary defensive camp ward

TRAVEL:
  rest camp             Return to your own camp from anywhere
  trailblaze to camp <name>  Visit another ranger's camp
  camps                 List all registered ranger camps

REQUIREMENTS:
- Must be in the wilderness (not city, indoors, or dock)
- An unpacked tent must be in the room
- You can only have one camp at a time
- Stocking, cooking, tending, and warding require being at your own camp

HOW TO SET UP CAMP:
  1. Learn the 'make rope' and 'make tent' skills
  2. Go to a grassy area: make rope
  3. Go to a wooded area: make tent
  4. Drop your packed tent: drop tent
  5. Set it up: unpack tent
  6. Establish camp: camp

Your tent will update to show "A makeshift tent (owned by <Name>)"
so other Rangers know whose camp this is.

RANGER NOMAD LIFE:
Rangers are wilderness nomads. Your camp is your home base in the
wild. Other Rangers can visit your camp, and you can visit theirs.
Use 'camps' to see all active camps, and 'rscore' to see your own.

SURVIVAL USE:
Use forage, mine, quarry, and skin to gather wildcraft supplies.
Camp stock turns kindling, clean water, and binding fiber into camp
supplies.

If your forage pouch fills with supplies you do not need, use
'forage stores' to review it and 'forage discard <component> [amount]'
to free room. Cooking, brewing, tending, and stocking camp also consume
wildcraft supplies.

Fish traps add fish catch to your camp stores. Fish catch is used by
fish stew and hunter feast.

Cooked foods:
  camp cook trail cakes
  camp cook smoked meat
  camp cook fish stew
  camp cook hunter feast

Brewed drinks:
  camp brew spring tea
  camp brew bark tonic
  camp brew smokeleaf infusion
  camp brew ranger draught

Cooked and brewed supplies scale with Ranger wilderness skill and level,
but they are field provisions: they do not save over logout or reboot.
Camp tend consumes fresh camp supplies, clean water, and medicinal scraps
for recovery while you are at your own camp.

